evidence: The density of the alloy, determined by the hydrostatic weighing method, was 7.07±0.03 g/cm 3 . After annealing at 1200˚C, the alloy had a single-phase B2 structure with the lattice parameter a=0.3304±0.0004 nm. The microstructure consisted of coarse (~400 μm) polygonal-shaped grains with clear boundaries (see a magnified insert in Fig.  3a ); the average chemical composition of the grains corresponded closely to the nominal composition (Fig.  3a , Table  1 ).
After annealing at 1200˚C, the alloy demonstrated the yield strength of 830 MPa and high compressive ductility (>50%) at room temperature (Fig.  4a, Table 2 ).
At 600°C, the yield strength decreased to 635 MPa, but the alloy retained the same work hardening capacity and high ductility (Fig.  4b ).
At 22°C, the yield strength increased by ~50% to 1250 MPa; the ductility reduced but maintained at a moderate level of 16% (Fig.  4a ).
